## Commit Message Format

Always generate commit messages in English following this structure:

### Pattern:

`<type>: <description in English>. <action> #<issue_number>`

### Types:

- feat: new feature
- fix: bug fix
- chore: maintenance tasks
- build: build system changes
- refactor: code refactoring
- docs: documentation changes
- style: code style changes
- test: test additions/modifications
- perf: performance improvements
- ci: CI/CD changes

### Actions:

- `closes #<number>` - when closing an issue
- `fixes #<number>` - when fixing a bug issue
- `#<number>` - when only referencing without closing

### Examples:

- `feat: add user authentication system. closes #123`
- `fix: resolve login validation error. fixes #456`
- `refactor: optimize database queries. #789`
- `chore: update dependencies to latest versions. closes #101`

### Instructions:

1. Always write commit messages in English
2. Use the issue type I specify (feat, fix, chore, etc.)
3. Convert the issue name/description to English if provided in Portuguese
4. Use the appropriate action based on my instruction:

- "fechar" or "close" → `closes #`
- "corrigir bug" or "fix bug" → `fixes #`
- "referenciar" or "reference" → `#`

5. Keep descriptions concise and descriptive
6. Use imperative mood (add, fix, update, etc.)
